{"word":"καταχράομαι","slug":"καταχράομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καταχράομαι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-χρήσομαι</el>) (<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>-κέχρημαι</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>-κέχρημαι</el> both in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> and <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> senses\n<el>(aor1 <el>-εχρήσθην</el>) </el><p/><div class='li250'><b>A. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make full use of, apply</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to use to the uttermost, use up</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to misuse, abuse</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b>of persons, <i>to make away with, destroy, kill</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>;—so aor1 <el>καταχρησθῆναι</el>, in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to pretend, allege</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li250'><b>B. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a><p/></div>"}]}